Hey, Emacs, we're -*-Text-*- mode!

The script "gokernel.sh" and the various other files in this directory
integrate the ftape version of this package into an v2.0 or v2.2 Linux
kernel.

Please don't use them, unless you know _exactly_ what they are
doing. They will overwrite the kernel sources without warning, and I
don't guarantee that the script work 100% OK. They did so for v2.0.36
and v2.2.2.

For the curious: run "gokernel.sh" like this:

gokernel.sh TOP_OF_LINUX_SOURCES TOP_OF_FTAPE_SOURCES

e.g.

gokernel.sh /var/tmp/linux-hacked-for-ftape /usr/src/ftape-4.x

Claus-Justus Heine <heine@instmath.rwth-aachen.de>

